
You are extending an existing Next.js video creator app called "Inkframe." 
The app already has: SVG scene generation via Claude API, a scene list, 
iframe preview, Zustand state, and a Node.js render server using 
WebVideoCreator + FFmpeg.

## GOAL
Add a scene type system so each scene is not just SVG — it can be one of 
five types, each with its own Claude generation prompt, HTML template, and 
UI. All scene types render in the same WVC pipeline unchanged since they 
all run in a browser.

---

## SCENE TYPES

Add a `type` field to the Scene model:
  "svg"      — existing pen-draw SVG animations (current behavior)
  "lottie"   — Lottie JSON animation as the main visual layer
  "motion"   — Motion (MIT) timeline-based animations on DOM elements
  "d3"       — D3.js data-driven animated charts/graphs
  "three"    — Three.js 3D scene

---

## 1. DEPENDENCIES TO INSTALL

Frontend (Next.js):
  npm install motion lottie-web @rive-app/canvas d3 three
  npm install @types/d3 @types/three

Scene HTML files load libraries via CDN (so WVC doesn't need them bundled):
  Motion:    https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/motion/11.11.9/motion.js
  Anime.js:  https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/animejs/3.2.2/anime.min.js
  Lottie:    https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bodymovin/5.12.2/lottie.min.js
  D3:        https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/7.9.0/d3.min.js
  Three.js:  https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/three.js/r128/three.min.js
  Rive:      https://unpkg.com/@rive-app/canvas@2.21.6/rive.js

