## 4. HTML TEMPLATES PER SCENE TYPE

When writing /public/scenes/{id}.html, branch on scene.type.

### Template: SVG (existing, unchanged)
Keep current template exactly as-is.
The auto-getTotalLength() script must remain.

### Template: Motion
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <style>
    * { margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }
    body { width:1920px; height:1080px; overflow:hidden; background:{bgColor}; }
    /* Scene-specific styles injected here by Claude */
    {styles}
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  {htmlContent}
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/animejs/3.2.2/anime.min.js"></script>
  <script type="module">
    import { animate, stagger, timeline } from "https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/motion/11.11.9/motion.js";
    {sceneCode}
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Template: Lottie
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <style>
    * { margin:0; padding:0; box-sizing:border-box; }
    body { width:1920px; height:1080px; overflow:hidden; background:{bgColor}; }
    #lottie-container { width:100%; height:100%; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="lottie-container"></div>
  <!-- optional SVG overlay layer for text/annotations -->
  <div id="svg-overlay" style="position:absolute;inset:0;pointer-events:none">
    {svgOverlay}
  </div>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/bodymovin/5.12.2/lottie.min.js"></script>
  <script>
    lottie.loadAnimation({
      container: document.getElementById('lottie-container'),
      renderer: 'svg',
      loop: false,
      autoplay: true,
      {lottieSource.startsWith('http') 
        ? `path: "${lottieSource}"` 
        : `animationData: ${lottieSource}`}
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Template: D3
```html
