## IMPLEMENTATION ORDER

1. Extend Scene type in Zustand store
2. Add type selector UI component (5 icon buttons)
3. Add HTML template functions (renderMotionTemplate, etc.)
4. Update writeSceneHTML to branch on type
5. Update /api/generate to route by type
6. Build D3 tab UI (data editor is the most complex)
7. Build Three.js tab UI
8. Build Lottie tab UI (file upload + URL)
9. Build Motion tab UI
10. Type badge on scene cards
11. Type-specific thumbnail timing
12. Test each type end-to-end in WVC export

---

## IMPORTANT NOTES

- Motion library CDN: verify the exact version exports 
  `animate`, `stagger`, `timeline` as named exports from 
  the browser bundle — test before deploying
  
- Three.js r128 via CDN: DO NOT use OrbitControls or other 
  extras — they are not on the Cloudflare CDN for r128. 
  Implement manual camera rotation in the animate loop instead.

- D3 v7 API: use d3.select, d3.scaleLinear, d3.axisBottom etc. 
  Claude should generate v7-compatible code. 
  Note: d3.event was removed in v7 — use event parameter in handlers.

- Lottie .json files can be large (1–5MB). Add a 5MB size limit 
  on upload and warn users.

- For the D3 data editor: debounce JSON validation by 500ms 
  so it doesn't fire on every keystroke.

- Monaco editor for code panels: lazy load it 
  (dynamic import) so it doesn't bloat the initial bundle.

- All five scene types must gracefully degrade in the browser 
  preview if generation fails — show a red error state with 
  the error message and a Retry button.
```